reviews: Really kind and helpful staff. I found it a very comfortable and exceptionally quiet and peaceful home after a very long and active day. 5 stars for a great staff. Pool was nice too. Once I figured our the correct exit from Gare de Lyon it was even better!

Everything about this hotel was good, except for a non-functional AC. I know it is Paris and most hotels do not even have an AC. But when you come back after a hectic day, the room feels very stuffy and claustrophobic without AC. When I complained at the front desk about this, she told me to open the window. And not only that, I was asked to sign on a form which says that I asked the hotel to open the window and if anything worst happens, I am responsible. Really ! This was a uniquely weird experience first time in my entire travel history across many countries.
Why cannot the hotel staff mention about this up front to all guests rather than waiting for them to complain?

Location:
Perfect ! The hotel is directly attached to the Gare De Lyon train station. Literally attached. We arrived in Paris by train from Zurich and were initially wondering about carrying our luggage. But it was just 2-3 minutes from getting down from the train in Hall-2 to the front desk of the hotel. Very very convenient. Even when we were roaming around Paris city, getting to the destination and getting back to the hotel was super easy. In most cases, Gare De Lyon is the starting point or the last point on the bus or the train. I highly recommend this hotel for the location.
Besides, you have every kind of shop, restaurants, cafes and what not at the Gare De Lyon station. So need not worry about buying stuff or going out to eat as a last minute plan.

Food:
Decent food. Good taste and good spread. We found the breakfast at Novotel Paris slightly better than Novotel Zurich. I can compare because we came from Novotel Zurich to Novotel Paris. The number of items in the breakfast were lesser but the taste and choice of dishes was slightly better. But Novotel Zurich is a far better hotel in all other aspects.

Room:
Besides the AC problem mentioned above, there was another minor issue. The bathroom is by default completely transparent. You have to press a button inside to make the glass opaque. But even this is not 100% opaque but it is acceptable. Lastly, the bathroom door has no lock, which is also ok, as no one would just walk-in inside a bathroom.
The size of the room was actually good, considering the kind of rooms you find in Paris. Three of us were able to sleep, walk around and keep our luggage comfortably in the room, so no complaints about the size of the room.

Overall, I would rate 3.5/5 for this hotel. I hope they fix the AC problem and it can be very close to 5 star rating.

The only thing I liked about this hotel room was that the view was better than many other hotels in Paris. I had a room on the higher floor with an open view of Place Henri Frenay. Also, I could open the windows to let some fresh air in, something that cannot be done at most other hotels where the windows are sealed shut. However, the hotel was very mediocre at best. Water backing up in the bathroom sink. The room had a very dated look, cheap furniture, a bit of a musty odor. The front desk staff was helpful. The best thing about this hotel is its location, right at Gare de Lyon. My Lyria train arrived late night, but I was able to conveniently exit the station from the Place Henri Frenay exit and quickly walk into the Novotel with my luggage. I only spent one night at this hotel. Overall, this hotel is not for tourists looking for a fancy Paris experience. This hotel is ok for a quick overnight stay, if you are going to use Gare de Lyon for transit, and if you cannot get a room at the Courtyard by Marriott, which is also close to Gare de Lyon.

Perfectly located next to the Gare de Lyon train station making my commute the next morning to Avignon super convenient. Lots of restaurants within walking distance. Room was spacious, clean, and functional. Booked an executive room with a large terrace. The terrace had a table and seating for four. Would definitely return.

This tired old hotel offers absolutely ZERO hospitality. The young women at the front desk should say Bonjour et bienvenue to arriving clients but are disinterested and ribotic instead. Rooms are small with small beds and strmnge uncomfortable pillows. Breakfast cost an absurd 21 Euros for industrail junk and is horribly overcrowded. And finally, this hotel is egregiously overpriced. You can do much much better elsewhere.

Booked a quadruple executive room for 6 nights of our stay in Paris. The hotel location is absolutely gorgeous - less than 2mins walk to Metro and bus stops, surrounded by different styles of restaurants, and supermarkets and convenient stores just around the corner.

Services were good - staffs were nice and helpful. Its Easter during our stay and its very lovely of them to put chocolate eggs in our room for egg hunting.

However, the room itself was not what I expected. First, its extremely stuffy. We had turned the air cond on to the max, but its still stuffy and at the end we have to open the window to get better ventilation. In addition, the air cond is extremely noisy at max and even you turn it down to min, you can still hear clearly the clicking sounds which is really irritating.

Second, the bathroom wall is a glass which can be turned frosted when someone uses it. Its a very common design among hotels nowadays, BUT I think its only half frosted!! Beware if you have teenager kids. In addition, the bathroom is 2-doored which you can clearly see the people inside through the crack in between.

Third, the water keeps leaking from the bath tub and the floor becomes very wet after bathing.

If you are looking for a convenient place to stay, Novotel Paris Gare de Lyon would be a good choice, no doubt. But I would definitely try other hotels for my next Paris trip for comfortability and decentness.

Btw, I received the final invoice through email after checking out, but interestingly its all in French, no English version at all!! Guess the management expects every guest knows French.

Stayed here 4 nights and though expensive as all these hotels in Paris are it was a very good location and staff were good.

There are plenty of local cafe restaurants/supermarkets, all well priced and good quality
- adjacent to the hotel.

Great location for all the various train stations etc.

Would stay here again

Pool was good also

I missed my train at the station and was very stressed. I wandered into the Novotel because I needed to wait somewhere for two hours and it looked nice from the outside. They happened to be serving breakfast so, instead of just wallowing in self-pity over a single cup of coffee, I found myself enjoying a lovely buffet with unlimited drinks (non-alcoholic), crepes and other assorted French pastries, hot meat and eggs, fruit and cheese. It was amazing, the staff were so nice, and I was able to relax and forgive myself for missing the train. Thank you Novotel!

Very nice historic building, very nice and safe location, nice and attentive staff, nice Holiday Inn Standard room with comfortable bed and bed linen and towels;
It was Easter days so the hotel offered for free a lot of chocolate eggs!
Special notice for the breakfast: really very rich, even scrambled eggs with black truffle - I have not seen in 5 stars hotels! Delicious...
The price is reasonable for Paris considering the quality you get!
Highly recommended!

Extremely bizarre choice of interior decoration - the bathrooms in our rooms had a glass wall that meant you could see the person in the bath or shower from the bedroom area! I mean, I know they're French and all but seriously?! My young teenage daughter did not want her siblings watching her shower and frankly my wife wasn't too keen on me seeing her wobbly bits either. No curtain or anything.

Nice hotel, normal-sized rooms for a central 4-star hotel. Very nice buffet breakfast. Obviously extremely convenient for the station. Price absolutely extortionate, but then I guess it's the same everywhere in that location. Only stayed one night so not much more to say.

The hotel is situated at a great location (next to a metro station) and has great facilities (swimming pool and a great gym). The members of staff are really friendly, and it is greta to enjoy a good glass of wine after a long day of enjoying the city of Paris.

I love this hotel for the pool which is great if you like laps (around 10m plus) and long opening hours (7am-11pm so great if working in Paris). Temp in water 27 degrees so if using it for kids they will find it a little chilly unless they swim. Breakfast I had included in error and it was great. Didn't need lunch after. Less great was the shampoo was empty in shower and generally not as friendly or affordable as on previous trips (pre inflation...)

Thoroughly enjoyable stay. Rooms were comfort and clean. Staff very helpful especially that bar manager who was first class. Baggage storage available onsite. Great access to subway and next to Gard de Lyon. Plenty of good eateries nearby and easy access to city centre and all its attractions. Kids loved the on site swimming pool.

Very nice hotel just in front of Gare de lyon and other attractions in the city of Paris.Rooms are quite spacious and Eiffel tower view from the room. Staff is very nice and supportive...good options for vegetarian people for breakfast.

Very close when arriving by TGV at Gare Lyon, nice indoor pool, friendly staff, easy access to town by metro (Arc de Triomph, Eiffel etc.). Nice room, very good beds, shower and with separate toilet. Very good breakfast buffet, but with some waiting queue and not enough Croissants for late comers...

Hotel is a good 3 star business hotel, room service is prompt, but limited. Staff are friendly. Breakfast is good. If you have a room facing the public square, i would recommend that you request to move to other orientation or you will get limited sleep.

Watch out for mosquitoes, as i was bitten several times.

Good location if you're looking to be close to the railway station and metro. We stayed for a couple of nights before going to Disneyland which is on RER line A, so proximity to the railway station was important.

I was in Paris with my family with two kids for 5 days and we have to acknowledge the excellent position, quality and service of Novotel Paris Gare De Lyon. Ideal location to get to the center thanks to the train (yellow line) as well as getting to Disneyland with the direct train RER A from Gare de Lyon.
Very clean hotel, with quality food for breakfast and a nice swimming pool ope until 23.00 at night.
Moreover talking about customer care and service, we forgot our home and car keys in the safety box of our room and it was shipped in 48 hours. Really thank you for all the care and service!

My family and I stayed here in August and I would recommend it. Our room was very clean and comfortable. The hotel at night was quiet,I didnt hear noises of people returning to rooms at night, like in other hotels.
Very convenient for the metro, to travel about in Paris, its only a 2 minute walk to the station from the hotel.
The choice of breakfast was very good and food was nice too. We didnt have the evening meals there, as went out each evening, so I cant comment on that. I would definitely stay in this hotel again.

Perfectly Ok hotel let down by poor service.
We booked as a family of 2 adults in the main bed with our child on the sofa bed for 4 nights, but throughout it was as though she didnt exist. We only ever had 2 towels, to the extent that after finding a spare high up in a cupboard it was taken away the next day. It was a bit odd to literally only have 2 towels (bar face towels) in the first place.
The worst thing then was the sofa bed was stripped and sheets not replaced on day 2. We raised this with the desk in the afternoon, who appeared disinterested. On our return at bedtime nothing had been done. We raised it with the desk again, who sent a man up with a double sheet, no idea what the issue was and initially expected us to make the bed.
We did later get an apology based on stained sheets rather than the obviously missing sheets when the man came in.
The curious possessiveness about towels continued when trying to ask for a swimming pool towel (as required, not least due to the minimal amount in rooms). 3 staff with 1 other customer were too busy to achieve this in 10 minutes. At the swimming pool were people who had taken up the 15 Euro offer for your own towel & dressing gown - you could see why.

These issues aside, the hotel is what you would expect from a Novotel, clean, reasonable room (slightly odd fully-see-through shower for families), well positioned.
The swimming pool, as advertised, is of course a nice attraction, though is not staffed or monitored in any way so prone to teenage dive-bombers.

So we chose this Novotel. The staff were incredibly nice and I am not much of a breakfast eater but I did like what I had. It was so easy to come and go to the train and they were cool about storing our luggage when it was an overnighter. I really appreciated the service here.

Enjoyed our stay here. The staff were really nice and the breakfast was fab. Train station next door. Access through Hall 2. You end up at the rear of the hotel. Staff were quite helpful in finding cabs etc

Novotel -Lyons.. is a great spot.. why? Location, convince to many things. We stayed for 5 nights.. when I booked I thought I did not choose close enough to everything .. the novotel de Lyons ( as there is many on paris)... this one was great... the spot was right beside the subway ( amazing access to get anywhere in paris.. and it was one of the bigger stops..., there was a grocery store around the corner, a Friday and Saturday market with fresh fruits, vegetables,shopping.. brilliant.. there was an amazing Shwarma place a stone throw away.. the food.. wow!)... the novotel had a breakfast that I paid for, for us... I paid for my boys to have breakfast as myself and my husband don't eat in the morning.. just a coffee... I went down with my boys and the greeter wanted to out all of us at a table... I had said.. just my boys.. she seated them and offered something to take back to the room?... I said just a coffee for myself and my husband ... she filled the glass mug for each of us... and said.... just leave it in the room when done!... thanked her for the 2 coffees and after we were done, brought the coffee mugs (massive in size and not those cardboard tiny things) back to the breakfast spot and tipped her... was so impressed by this chain hotel... as we don't stay in chains and want to see other locations wglhile we travel... cannot say enough about the novotel Lyons.. impressed! I travel for work and have stayed in many hotels, motels, airbnb, chains... this was the first time I have stayed at the novotel.. I will be trying other locations during my travels for work... thankbyouvfor being so gracious and offering an umbrella when it rained 1 day, thank you for bringing extra towels for us to our room, thank you for that coffee... it's the simple things... and that is not forgotten. Kindly

We had the worst flight issues - cancellations, delays, and our luggage was lost and never found- but the staff here made up for our issues with their excellent customer service! They helped us find clothes late at night, let us use their phone chargers, helped with late checkout, amongst so many other things (Especially Carla and Hugo- they were so sweet and went above and beyond!) . The breakfast was delicious, the pool was a must for anyone traveling with kids, and they even have a kids corner with video games!!! Love this place!

Great hotel located adjacent to the Fare de Lyon.
Room was nice with comfortable bed, good shower, mini-fridge and safe. Breakfast was very good with a nice assortment of breads, cereals, yogurt, hot food, juices, water and coffee/tea.
The only thing that could be improved is the temperature of the hot foods; the eggs were lukewarm as they were in a covered casserole-type dish.
There were many cafes and brasseries in the area adjacent to the hotel.

Great location, just right next to the train station, not even a minute walk. Breakfast with good varieties of food. Very friendly and helpful staffs. We would definitely come back to stay here when traveling to Paris.

Slow check in. Good disabled access. Great room. Lots of space for my wheelchair. Good adapted wet room.

BUT

Terrible urine smell in the outdoors colonnade

Under the sheets was a cheap, nasty, plastic film mattress protector. Talk about making us sweat.

Heating hard to control.

Combine plastic with over warm room and sleeping was uncomfortable.

I appreciate the need for covid protections but this was the worst Ive come across.

Was originally booked into another hotel but due to a technical issue, we were relocated to this hotel which was a higher star rating. The hotel itself is situated centrally right beside the Gard De Lyon Station and walking distance to many bars and restaurant which is ideal. The foyer is grand and the bar area sits in the middle which was reasonably priced. Room size was great and all mod cons. Overall a lovely unexpected stay and would recommend this hotel for anyone wishing a break in Paris - it does also have a gym, small swimming pool and kids play area all on site.

Average hotel. small room view with limited windows with no view. Near Gare De Lyon but so many paths to the station and a little complex! Staff are not so polite. Outside of hotel is not clean. The best point is breakfast.

The front-desk receptionist didn't even look up when I arrived, but asked for my name, then stopped to chat for a few minutes with a colleague, and then asked me my name again because she'd forgotten it> So ZERO welcome, and a really rude attitude began this stay. Mattress in the room was awful, as were pillows, and overall this place is very very overpriced for being essentially a rundown two-star business hotel. The only reason they get away with such poor service and bedding is that its convenient to the train station. GO ELSEWHERE!!!!!!!

The only thing this hotel has going for it is it's convenient location next to the Gare de Lyon. Otherwise, our recent stay was very poor for a variety of reasons. Check-in staff were unfriendly, inefficient and almost rude, and front desk staff in general were unhelpful and robotic during our visit. Worse, the bedding quality here is just awful. I don't understand how Group Accor manages to buy such awful mattresses, but this is a problem that cuts across all of their brands. Breakfast was ordinary, especially for the price, and overall, this is a two-star hotel charging four-star prices, probably because so many of the people who stay here are on a company expense account. I would not stay here again, and neither should you.

Great Hotel, friendly, helpful staff.

Wanted to give a 5 star rating but app did not go past 4.

Very clean, comfortable rooms, easy check in at self standing stations.

Walking distance. to train station and metro.

Super breakfast buffet but rest of menu does not have a big selection.

My sister stayed for a night in this hotel few days ago. I was not aware that I booked another room on the same day. My sister tried to explain to the hotel that I was not aware of this and if they can refund the other charges they made.. They told my sister they can't refund it back due to their policy, instead they offered another night for my sister to stay and pay extra 20 Euros. 200 Euros to charged in a room that is not used is for me not right... It's a lot of money to take for another booking that I am not aware of..

Well what can I say? It's a simple hotel close to the Lyon station. Nothing special more than a novotel franchise hotel. What is special is that is overpriced for sure. It's the kind of hotel used of working conventions etc. In the surrounding areas I wouldnt advice to be around late in the night. Its filled with homeless people, rats and people peeing literally even in the door of the hotel. For this price (300 euros per night) you can do much much better. Minusculous rooms with normal service and nothing special to highlight. If we are talking 80 euros I would say hey it's good for the value and price but 300? This is insane. Maybe because its paris? I dont know or even understand the value of paris anyway. It all smells to urine, its dirty and not a place I would come anytime soon. In any case, this is my verdict valuable as any other person. I work for my money and I just want to make everyone aware that this is not worth the price. That's all.

I booked this hotel for my upcoming PARIS visit in late August 2021 and then realized I've entered a missing night in my dates during the booking. I booked one of their "Book with confidence" rates which is fully refundable up to 3 days before arrival. I went ahead and cancelled the reservation and have been expecting my refund since then. They charge you the second you book, but when it comes to your refund it's all a big silence. I understand refunds may take 1-2 weeks, but there is no communication from the property whatsoever. You cancelled your booking and then what happens to your prepayment?? I've sent them emails, reached out on their Facebook and Instagram and did I get any replies? ZERO. Very frustrating experience. You at least want to ask someone if they have processed your refund or not but not a single reply!

Its "ok" you know what you're getting from a Novotel.
There are major renovations on going at the hotel, but it doesn't affect your stay if I am honest.
Check in was fine, polite staff, room clean and comfortable.
Location is good.
However, why would you put a family in a room at the back of the hotel overlooking the busy road, so that every car horn, or siren wakes you up? Seems a silly policy to me, and something that we didn't realise until we got back after a budy day sightseeing so it was too late to move.

I'd go back, but request a room at the front.

We couldnt make our booking in December due to the protests in Protests, yourselves informed that we have until March to rebook. When we contacted you to rebook you took over a week to reply. We have sent numerous emails requesting our refund because you didnt honour your deal but we havent heard anything back for almost two weeks now.

Stayed for 3 nights in a nice room, for 4 of us.
A bit shocked when we arrived, as the whole lobby is undergoing refurbishments. I was not informed about this. Reception was hidden in a lower part of the building. Check in was fast but a bit cold. Answered our question and that was it. Breakfast was nice with wide choice. Location is great as just 1 minute from Gare de Lyon where you have everything: metro, RER, trains and buses. Supermarket and lots of restaurants close by.

Stayed one night before an early train to the Alps and in that respect the location is absolutely ideal. Some nice restaurants etc are a reasonably close walk as well. The rooms are basic and on the small side but nicely done and fit for purpose if the trains are your main reason for staying. Do note though that there are MAJOR building works currently going on so it's a bit of a mess and no facilities available other than check-in and the room. We booked a while ago and only received a follow-up email afterward advising us. We didn't mind too much given the purpose but it should have been noted in advance. We weren't even offered a discount or anything which is a shame. However, if catching an early train again would probably stay given the convenience.

We stayed here a few years ago and loved it, hence why without hesitation we booked this for our four night stay no refund no cancellation allowed. After we booked only then we found out there were major works and the pool was closed. We tried to get a refund as we specifically wanted a hotel with a pool. They would not allow us to. When we arrived pretty much the whole of the ground floor was shut with major works, dusty and no lounge area. The restaurant is in a soulless room upstairs and the childrens play area is tiny, not like before. We still have 3 nights to go.

Room 512 stay 04 to 06 Feb. This in my opinion is close to robbery, and false advertisement, You have a small banner indicating works are going one ,,,, But these are MAJOR works. There is no reception. At the 5th floor after a 14 hrs leg flight and the noise is just crazzy !!!!!! HOW IS THIS POSSIBLE FOR PAYING THE FULL PRICE.
I can't recognize my original country anymore. It seems scam is everywhere. Paye et tait toi ! I am doing an effort staying at Accor when in Europe. Just noticed the Marriott on the other side of the block .... At least I know where I sleep next time.

There is a bed and a pull out sofa which is pretty comfortable but the actual hotel I would rate a 3/10. When booking the hotel they don't warn you that they're completely under construction. Their gym is also a joke. They have 2 treadmills, an elliptical, a bike, and one machine you can use to pull bars down... but they literally no free weights. Honestly, I've never seen a worse gym. I recommend staying at Hotel Parisianer next door.

We stayed 2 nights in October, during renovations.
Highlights: good location. Walking distance to plenty of nice restaurants, little grocery store for things like water, light snacks. Can't beat the location to the subway station, walk out the door and it's there. I had seen a lot of people comment they perhaps felt unsafe walking to the subway, we never felt this. Traveled with 2 boys aged 10 and 8, and did not feel worried about their safety at any time, and were even outside in evening at times.
Rooms: not impressive. Wifi is non-existent. The first night I went down to front desk to ask if there was a problem and told there was not. However, upon check out a couple days later, even the front staff computers were not working well, the attendant kept saying "sorry, my computer does not seem to be working today", creating quite a backup of people. She even gave us a chocolate bar for our wait (I hadn't complained, but she seemed frustrated so I guess felt like feeding us). The lack of wifi actually impacted our trip, for things like booking tickets for museums on the day, or looking up schedules for transportation or status on trains out of the city, or even recommendations on restaurants. We had brought a laptop to keep the kids occupied on down-time, we never were able to use it.
Also with the room: we had bought a nice bottle of wine and some cheese, baguette and brought back to room. I know the following is customary for most hotels, but this is Paris after all...we just had plastic cups to use. Kinda less than the Paris-vibe. Also, after using the 4 we were given the first day, they didn't replace them with new ones the next day. So, we then had even zero plastic cups. All of a sudden we were wishing we had the tacky plastic. We should've known since no one came to clean the room, we had to do it all, make our own beds (yeah, I know, entitled, but again, this is usually what happens in a hotel).
And finally, noted in other reviews, the shower is bizarre. The glass is opaque. This may make me a prude, but having 2 boys aged 10 and 8, I don't feel like being on display when bathing. I actually ended up showering in the dark before they woke up to prevent any weird memories of their mom. I was able to figure out how to make the glass opaque, but you can still see a silhouette. Just an FYI if you're travelling with a friend that you don't feel like over-sharing with.
Not sure if I'd recommend it, I definitely will not look to stay here again, but if you're ok with these inconviences, then price and location isn't bad.

We came with my family and 2 sons for 4 days and this is a great hotel. The service was excellent and location is brilliant. The main train station is right next to the hotel and we used it everyday! I would for sure book this hotel again and hope to be back soon. Only issue was that the pool was closed during the time we came but the hotel provide a birthday cake for my wife birthday.

Proved to be an excellent location due to limitations of transport due to strikes. Excellent service, helpful and smiling stuff willing to assist, the room was ready early as we arrived in the morning, very clean rooms and the cleaning ladies deserve the best and a quite rich breakfast. Enjoyed every day and night during our Xmas holidays.

This hotel is conveniently located right next to Gare de Lyon and would have been amazing if the public transportation strike was not currently underway.

We approached front desk multiple times for alternative transportation solutions to Disneyland and La Vallee Village which they just told us "strike" or "RATP not working" and we had to find our own alternatives. They were not helpful in this manner.

The room itself was lovely and spacious and if you are planning on spending your days touring this is a lovely hotel to come back to in the evenings. We were not directly affected by any of the construction.

This is a very beautiful place that u could enjoy your meal in a romantic atoumospher and pretty good staff.
About of meal i only could enjoyable . Some times you need such this place to go for relaxation and make a good time for your girlfriend

We were Lucky to book this hotel next to the station Gare de Lyon, which saved us during a period of strikes in metro in Paris... Nearby we had wonderful boulangeries, Coffee shops etc. The hotel staff was really polite and helpful.There were some disantvantages through.. The room for 4 was really small and the extra beds were not comfortable at all. In fact, on our first night, one of them was right on the floor.... My son did not like that matress at all!.They offered us a small bottle of water for 4....which wa not enough... And upon check in, they Block 320 euro on your card... Everything else was great, if you like a central hotel and a clean, safe family hotel.

To be avoided until March
I booked a month ago with Accor directly on the phone hoping to have a hotel with a pool. I had stayed there years ago and loved the pool. Nobody informed me of the ongoing works during my booking and even the emails I received after did not mention that the pool does not work.

When I complained to the staff on arrival she kindly upgraded me to the next class of rooms without me asking which was nice but this did not compensate for the inconvenience in my opinion. I also found that both the bar and restaurant were relocated during the works which is really not very nice either.

I find this simply dishonest and I mentioned it to the director who told me that I should have been informed. This was not the case. He apologized and kindly sent me a chocolate bar.

I paid 230 euros per night which was way too much for the service and product offered. After this bad experience I have a rather bad image of the Accor group and wonder whether I will remain a member.

We had the great misfortune to stay at the Novotel Paris Gare de Lyon recently.

If you enjoy a hotel experience that involves you being exposed to extensive renovation work involving use of both a makeshift bar and restaurant area, closure of a swimming pool and a dusty, dirty reception desk area, this is the hotel for you. Noise booming around you throughout the day from around 9:00am just completes the thoroughly unimpressive experience at this hotel currently.

We have stayed at this hotel quite often in the past, mostly because of its proximity to the Gare, and found it to be reasonable enough. Strangely this past visit we had problems trying to book online. In the end our booking had to be arranged through the Accor group phone service. We cant help but think it was deliberate that we were prevented from becoming aware of the major renovation work going on as a result.

To add to the unacceptable treatment we encountered at this hotel, which appallingly expects guests to put up with thoroughly substandard conditions, the hotels General Manager, Serge Lenormand appears to have ignored an email written by us to him. Yes I suppose I can see why he would be disinclined to respond to an email expressing dissatisfaction about the sorry state of the hotel he is responsible for as it currently stands. More a matter of take the accommodation money and run.

Thankfully there are many good hotels in this district that treat guests respectfully, unlike the Paris Gare de Lyon Novotel that clearly has greater interest in profits than the comfort of its guests.

We were a large group of 14 ranging from a 2 year old to grandparents and this hotel met everyones needs for the week we were there visiting from Chicago. We had 5 rooms and all our party had no complaints really. Breakfast was not included in our room rate and was a bit pricey but the overall selection was great and was good, we ate there twice. Otherwise the area is super convenient to public transport. Gare de Lyon station is right out the back entrance and we were able to get to all the sights in Paris and Disneyland by just using the train system. Our kids also used the pool one evening and they really enjoyed the break after a busy week. There is plenty of food/bars in the area just do your research before you visit. We genuinely felt safe in the area but used our common sense just like any major city. Wed recommend this hotel and would use it again should the opportunity arise.

This is a very nice hotel. The decor is nice & the rooms are comfy. But and however this hotel is noisy AF! I had to complain to reception at 4am because of drainage noise! They moved me to a next room. Also to add, there were renovations taking place in the morning and there were no prior warnings of noise. The noise ruined my experience. Hotels are supposed to be relaxing

We stayed there after a long flight from Asia. Overall pricey for what you get. The room can indeed accomodate a family of 4 but it is small. The family breakfast buffet has good food but decor is so so. The restaurant downstairs was not a good experience (slow service and average food). I think I paid almost total 400 EUR for 1 night ! (including early check in charges)

Stayed here for six nights end of October 2019, family of four. My son and I were bitten by Mosquiteos. My son was very badly bitten. Have the photos to prove it. Complained to the Manager who offered a refund on the breakfasts but really should have refunded the cost of the hotel. Given I paid for a family of four, there was only one bottle of complimentary water provided per day I found it pretty shabby. Advised the manager that WWII has been over for quite some time and queried him on the water rations. I was told it was hotel policy which is BS as I have stayed in other Novotels around the world and bottles of water are not even an issue. Works out at less than 200mils per person per day for a family of four. Fridge full of water after complaint but it's a bit crap to go cap in hand asking for this basic stuff.

It is a good location and I have stayed here before staff are very friendly but I was not aware of the major renovations and the complete gutting of the downstairs restaurant and swimming pool during our stay. Only a problem on our last morning when grandson was not well so wanted to sleep longer. However all our needs were met & I was able to take his breakfast to our room.

We stayed at this hotel for this visit as we had stayed there on a previous visit and really enjoyed it. This time we were a little disappointed. There was a strong smell of urine in the street at the front of hotel and homeless people living/sleeping nearby. Another gripe I have is the hotel did not provide toiletries in the room. This was the only Accor hotel in Europe we experienced this. I not sure why this was the case as we had been provided with them on previous visits. We had not brought this stuff with us to save on suitcase weight. The hotel did provide some on request, however after a long flight all we wanted was a shower and had to wait for soap and shower gel to be delivered. It was not a mistake either as we were not supplied any the next day and when I queried was informed that only executive rooms were provided with them. At over $350 per night I think this is the least they can provide to weary travellers without having to ask. That said there are nice cafes/restaurants near by and the hotel has easy access to public transport.

me &my daughter visited Novotel gare de Lyon from 28.10. - 01.11.
We are more than dissappointed about our stay. The renovation work Inside the hotel is causing a closure of all common rooms.
The Pool and Kids area, because of that i choose this rather expensive hotel was totally closed. I didn't get any information before and not even at Check in. Just when i asked about the Pool...
The works inside the hotel were so loud at day, that sleeping for my child was impossible. Opening windows is also a bad idea, there is also a construction Side in front of the hotel.
They offered to refund the breakfast, which i Just got after asking again and again...and the breakfast is less than 10% of the price of the room. Excuse me that is no compensation for closing the whole hotel. No Restaurant, no Pool,no Cafeteria, no Kids area.
Improvised Breakfast room was totally overcrowed...that is Not okay for 200 a night hotel!

This hotel is right next to Gare de Lyon. It could not be any closer. However, it is quite sound proof and quiet. We had a coffee machine and a minibar that was refilled daily with a variety of drinks. The main bed as well as the extra bed were comfortable. Whenever we spoke to the staff, it came across like it was a chore for them. This includes reception and housekeeping. I hope that this could improve. If the staff were friendlier, I would have scored 5 stars.

There were more than 10 mosquitoes inmy room on my first night and I requested to changed another room. Although the staff was surprised, she changed the room for me sincerely.
After the few days trip, I back to this hotel again ( as fully paid, failed to cancel the booking). When I check out, I highly requested different direction from that mosquito room. But when I checked in again, my room is same floor and near that mosquito room . I needed to beg her for another room as she said the mosquitoes were everywhere and showed me another mosquito in the check in counter. Finally I begged for a room in highly floor.
Actually we did comment in their questionnaire, but there is no reply. Seems all the staff are very consistent. They might think I am crazy and why would surprise hotel with mosquitoessss. Maybe this hotel is not suitable for me as I dont accept more than 10 mosquitoes in a hotel guest room.

Firstly the positive, the hotel room was clean. But ...

Please be careful with this hotel. We booked and paid through hotels.com in late July and have been really looking forward to our stay in early October. We chose this hotel over others as it had a pool and the idea was after long days sightseeing in paris we would relax at the pool in the evening. I received an email the day before we arrived to tell us they were pleased to inform us that the hotel was going through a major refurbishment and the pool will be closed until next year!! Well how disappointed our family was, we had already packed our swimming costumes! This was a major refurbishment and had obviously been planned for months so we paid for facilities that they knew would not be available. I would never have picked this hotel had I known. Since returning we have contacted hotels.com to complain and ask for compensation for the facilities we expected and paid for but did not receive. The hotel have flatly refused. This hotel was knowingly missold to us by novotel and they are refusing to accept any responsibility.

Hotel is very smart and charming. I liked service and staff so much. I stayed here for 2 nights but it was nice. I also used my accor points there in which assured my points for usage easily. The staff is very nice and helpful. The rooms are very tidy and clean

The hotel was undergoing some refurbishment and there were workmen working in the next room. Lots of noise, plastic sheeting in the corridors. Although tea and coffee were provided in the room there were only paper cups, rather spoit the experience. Overall disappointing for the price.

We stayed for one week. In spite of building works in the hotel, we met really friendly hotel-people from Novotel. Many thanks for your cheerful engagement during this hard time for you. The only missing point from our point of view was the below average heating in the hotel room.

This hotel is right at the corner of Gare de Lyon. Very conveniently located.

What shocks me most is I find disposable paper and plastic cups in the room and in the toilet. Not a single decent ceramic cup or glass you can use.

Besides, it doesn't mention about the massive renovation the hotel is going through on hotels.com. It was very noisy when we checked-in yesterday. Fortunately there is no renovation during the weekend.

The room is of decent size but I wish there would be more storage space in the room. Not a single drawer can be found in the room. Breakfast is average. Nice tea bags they use but the water is not hot enough.

whenever we visit Paris (I come from here), our train arrives at Gare de Lyon. As I have two small kids (3 & 5) having a hotel right next to the train station is fantastic. Especially if the room are nice, the restaurant good and the staff helpful.

I would not say it's the best hotel I ever stayed in, but we come here (it's the 6th time)

This Novotel is just around the corner from the train station and metro line making it an easy choice for getting around the city. The rooms are comfortable and the staff very friendly. Although I was traveling on business, I would recommend this for a family vacation as well.

The hotel is ideally located for Gare de Lyon railway station commuting. We had a very good short stay experience. The hotel staff were excellent, informative and helpful and the hotel facilities were very good.

We loved this Hotel... great room, great friendly and helpful staff located centrally in Paris, close to public transport and the train station - great food - great value for money which we would have no problem recommending to anyone

I stay at this hotel frequently- I like the rooms and the location - but - at this moment - the lobby is under construction - so things are a little difficult. The line for breakfast is long, in fact too long. I found breakfast elsewhere. It is unclear how to get to the pool (or if it still exists).

Was a little apprehensive about this hotel based on reviews. However the room was lovely(executive room).The staff were friendly.We picked this hotel purely on location as we only had a 1 night stay and were catching a train to Zurich next morning.We ate at the restaurant for dinner and breakfast. The dinner menu was limited, breakfast was good.The streets surrounding the hotel were very busy and we went for a little explore, however you would not walk around late at night. It was very easy to enter the station the next day without dragging our bags up any stairs. If you exit hotel out front onto main square and turn right , there are a number of glass doors further along that lead onto lower level of station.

I think this hotel is the closest you can get to Gare De Lyon, literally steps away from the gare it is highly convenient for passengers on short stays. The staff is very  international  and efficient. Will solve any of your problems in a matter of minutes, you will definitely experience a no fuss check in and check out. The superior double room is good and very spacious and clean. The tv screen is impressive and will almost make you want to stay in instead of going out! However, what is really sad is that, despite the fact that the room was on the 4th floor it wasnt sound proof and all the noise walk us up at 430 am!!! Maybe one should make it a point to ask for a higher floor when doing a reservation.
The hotel provides room service and a caf as well as restaurant. So one can eat or drink before or after a train journey. Its not gourmet food but its not bad either. Like the hotel it could use a little  coup de jeune  meanwhile it does a beautiful job.

We stayed one night here en route to Lucerne. The hotel is very conveniently placed, right next to the railway station. The check-in was friendly and efficient. Our room was on the 6th floor and described as a double. It was very small, okay for one night but I wouldnt have wanted to stay longer in such a small space. The room was spotlessly clean. There were no tea or coffee making facilities, or mini-bar, which would have been welcome. We planned to eat in the hotels Brasserie but when we went down we were told that it was closed as they were doing some work there. My husband is not very mobile so it was very inconvenient for us to have to go outside to find a restaurant. The reception were surprised when we told them the restaurant was closed so it had obviously been done a short notice. They suggested room service, but that wasnt an option in our tiny room, with one small table and one chair. One other thing worth mentioning, we could hear a noise which took us a while to identify. We finally realised that it was the rumble of the trains coming into the station. Didnt hugely bother us, but worth thinking about if you are booking this hotel - ask for a room on the other side away from the railway. Breakfast was really nice with everything anybody could possibly need, which made us even more upset that we didnt get the opportunity to try the dinners!

This hotel is all about location, next to the station and the Seine and with lots of shops and restaurants nearby it is a great base.
Yes there are some homeless guys who sit drinking near the station entrance but they did not cause any problems for me personally.
The staff in the hotel are really nice and the cleaning staff are exceptional.
It was a nice to have a pool in Paris but the only down side were the changing rooms which were virtually non- existent , essentially the toilet with lockers outside.
Rooms were spotless and large, especially by Paris standards.
Only slight negative was that only one bottle of water was provided for a family of four.
I would stay here again if I wanted to explore that part of Paris.

Strategically located near the Gare de Lyon train station and the Paris metro, this is a great property with nice, clean rooms and good service. The hotel has a nice pool with great gym facilities. The restaurant was good, but during breakfast it was somewhat overrun with many children that seemed a bit out of control at times and excited about the pancake maker. Aside from this, I would stay here again on the strength of its location, spacious rooms and good service.

Stayed two nights at the Novotel at Gare de Lyon. If you leave the station by the side exit (via Hall 2) you will immediately find the hotel.

Our room was comfortable. Unusual shower in that, at first, the glass wall between the shower and the bedroom is clear, but at the press of the button becomes opaque. Tea / Coffee making facilities, fridge and safe in room.

Swimming pool is small and deep. Most of the pool is 2.1m deep and I was soon out of my depth.

Table football available in reception area, there also had internet terminals and a childrens area.

Area best avoided after dark (hotel does employee a security guard). Too many drunks and people sleeping rough. Area by one door to reception also smelt strongly of urine.

It 's a very good hotel for 4 starts services but for the Location: it's near gare de Lyon , but gare de Lyon street is very popular and unsafe in the night (my opinion).
Room are very clean and large enough.
There is a pool that all time kids can enjoy it with a large reception room with baby foot games etc

The hotel is comfortable, well located, an excellent breakfast, easy access to public transport, good restaurants, supermarkets, pharmacies nearby. A few meters from the Seine. A good hotel in a nice place.

I start by saying it is extremely close to the metro which is great because that was the main source of transportation for me and my family (metro 2-minute walk) super convenient.

The rooms are nice but I was a bit small, I was naive when I booked for three people in the room me, my wife and daughter; it felt cramped which is why it does not get a 5-Star from me. Another thing if you use washcloths to shower bring your own because they did not supply plus every time I ask all I got was a hand towel (lesson learned) extremely clean accommodations. Remember I said I had three people in the room they only supplied (1) bottle of water every day even after I told them there are three people in the room.

The restaurant staff, tables, overall service was FABULOUS my hat is off to them when I made a reservation I included breakfast (RECOMMEND) it is a fantastic way to start your day plus what was offered was great.

The outside of the hotel is ok scenery it is a concrete courtyard and the local's hangout there even when we came late it felt safe. So this is a hotel that convenient, affordable and comfy to stay at.

This is a good option if you would like to visit paris with children. The hotel has a small pool and a game area for the children. Rooms are expensive, but you will hardly find any cheaper in Paris. Close to the subway, you will find yourself 15 minutes from most main attractions. The back side of the hotel is not very nice though. There is no danger or something, but everywhere around the hotel it smells like urine and its noisy (skate boards, voices, etc.). But I would definitely recommend and go again.

Place is very, very well managed. Customer service is beyond expectation. Really good place, clean with good selection for breakfast. They have bar on premises and pool, as well as, kids room where kids can play games. Pool open 24/7, Gym until 22:00. Staff is amazing! Computer with printer available for use as well.

The type of hotel that wants to charge families for the smallest of things, even a small cup of milk for a 1 year old baby (3.5 Euros by miserable barman) - I have never been charged for toddler milk especially as we had purchased lots of other drinks at the bar already. The man would not listen, first he gave me hot milk even though I told him 3 times I wanted cold, then got angry with me!
We were watched and followed around at the breakfast bar and my niece was told she was not allowed to fill her own water bottle at the buffet. We decided not to eat or drink anything at the hotel after this apart from the breakfast which we had already paid for.
The was one man at check-in who was helpful but everyone else was completely miserable. Not the greatest selection at breakfast either. Disappointing for somewhere that claims to be 4 star.

Nice rooms. Modern and well kept. Good hotel in price range. Multi lingual helpful staff. Pool & air con was good in the summer heat. Good kids zone in reception and kids outside play area on the non road/station side.

Hotel next to train station and easy to get around.However did not feel safe in general area of hotel after dark ,undesirables congregate on plaza in front of train station and entrance to hotel.wanted to go out for a walk just after dark and turned round staying in safety of hotel.The hotel itself is very family friendly and a separate breakfast room is available for children,characters and balloon artists come to breakfast room along with staff being friendly and helpful.The rooms are comfortable and a free safe is provided.pool open 24/07 and small gym until 22,00hrs.Unfortunately many other train stations in Paris seem to have similar issues and dozens of criminals stare at people leaving the stations looking for their next victim. The police should move them on as they have no good reason to be there.

I booked this hotel because it had a swimming pool and we were able to have breakfast included. The rooms were very clean and comfortable. The motel is close to bus and metro stops. The staff were friendly and helpful.

Stayed 2 nights. Everything is good but the cleanliness around the hotel building is average (also smell like Paris). Breakfast for Adult costs EUR 16 but for a family with 2 kids, average is about EUR 8 per person and is reasonable.

Very good location, clean, comfy, nice beds, nice bathroom, friendly staff, good breakfast, we will stay in the future, nice TV set, value for money. Nespresso machine, not very big room but comfortable

fab location next to train station, nice pool. clean and tidy. good breakfast and helpful staff. stayed with children. found lovely tradition restaurant just around the corner. best thing is location! kids loved the 'maggic glass wall'

The hotel is perfectly situated next to the Gare De Lyon. Perfect for exploring Paris. From start to finish the staff were brilliant, always quick to meet our needs. The room was spacious with a great view if the square. The breakfast included each morning was perfect with 2 rooms available, one being a family room equipped with entertainers. Nothing like starting the day dancing with a Smurf. The pool was a great addition which the kids enjoyed plus the kids area in the lobby was a lifesaver. Great hotel with lovely staff.

Paris, known for its small apartments or accommodation at very expensive rates, especially over the summer. But I soon changed my perspective on that when we went to stay at the Novotel Gard de Lyon. Rooms were a good size for a family of 4 sharing. It was clean and comfortable, breakfast was very French, lovely croissants, cheeses, yogurts etc. what made it more appealing, was that we were able to take the train or metro conveniently from our doorstep. ( love Europe and their transport systems.) restaurants and supermarkets 2 within walking distance.

Very comfortable rooms and amazingly helpful staff. Best breakfast in Paris. The best part is it's proximity to Gare De Lyon train station. You can just pull your luggage to Hall 2 of the station. Lots of things to do nearby.

Mixed feelings about this hotel as we had to move room due to a couple of issues. The hotel is in a good location and the room was clean and comfortable but the matter of plastic glasses & paper cups for the mini bar & coffee machine does not lend itself to this Accor brand. Presumably this is being done on cutting hotel costs and increasing margins but by doing so does not sit well with environmental concerns.

Stayed for 4 nights with family and friends. Was an amazing experience at the property. Very good location and courteous staff. Next door to Gare de Lyon metro makes it ideal to quickly move around the city
My son liked the indoor swimming pool the most. The breakfast spread was equally nice. Definitely recommend.

We booked 2 rooms here as we were arriving late by train. The hotel is adjacent to the station. The rooms were impeccably clean, roomy and bathroom had all the amenities we needed for our stay. The beds are unbelievably comfortable. Check in was quick; staff very friendly.

Amazing hotel. It is fairly priced with a nice gym and pool. My children enjoyed the lobby Foosball table and the video games. I is in a great neighborhood, with excellent restaurants and a nearby market. My only problem was that it is VERY easy to get lost driving to it. The street is a small one-lane street lined with motorcycles most of the time. 10 feet away and parallel to it is a 3 lane huge road that goes down to a parking garage and on to other locations. I turned onto the huge street 5 times before I even noticed that the real street was even there. Its easy to miss. Hotel staff was very helpful, great English (our French is barely there). Rooms were comfortable and good size. Beds very nice.

We stayed in Novotel Gare de Lyon in the week leading up to Easter. The reception area is very nice, with the staff being helpful and speak very good English. We arrived at about 7pm and received our room key straight away. However, the room was very small for a family room for 4, but was decorated nicely and was very modern. We had an issue with privacy, as the bathroom was very open. The glass between the bathroom could alternate between see through and frosted, but even when frosted you could see the outline of the person in the shower/bath - not very good for a family room! Apart from this, the hotel was very good. We only ate in for breakfast, but the selection was good and tasty, but you had to get their early or it would be very busy, the hotel is in a good area, near to Bastille and lots of restaurants, shops and bars, including some big brand shops like Sephora. Also very close to a metro station which meant you had easy access to all the tourist attraction, and a direct train to DisneyLand Paris! Overall, a very good hotel but better for a couple rather than a family.

Just had a wonderful family weekend. Lovely rooms, incredibly comfortable beds and the swimming pool was a big hit with the kids! Also breakfast was very good! And we found the location very good. Will definitely be back!

I've been 3 days on a business trip. To highlight the location very convenient just close to the Train Station and the area surrounded of several restaurants. Got surprised of a number of families (perhaps the holidays season) with kids - the hotel is well prepared for families, with swimming pool and areas for kids.

Stayed with wife and two kids for four nights recently and thought it was nice. Good location, friendly staff and nice clean rooms. The one negative thing was the breakfast which I would recommended to not buy and in stead use one of the many nearby restaurants. Not much to choose from, not the best quality of food, and rather expensive. My kids eat a lot and is not difficult with food, but here there was not a lot to choose from.

We stayed at the hotel seven days during the record heat wave in Paris. The rooms are modern with great air conditioning that work perfect. Theres a safe and a refrigerator which was supplied with two bottled waters daily which were definitely needed, appreciated, and used. Housekeeping was good, although we would receive replacement towels for two instead of three. We had the breakfast included which was very good, but after seven days, we were down to a couple croissants and coffee. To us, the location was great; the hub of Gare de Lyon, metro stops, and Rer. Its a very busy area, but it was convenient and we felt safe at all times. We would definitely stay here again.

This hotel is next to one of the largest train stations in Paris. In front of the hotel entrance you will be welcomed by homeless people sleeping next to the entrance and other shady characters lurking about.

The hotel is a machine. If it works, you get what is promised, if it doesnt, there is no will or empowerment in the staff to remedy your troubles. In our stay it accumulated to:

Our room was not cleaned from the last guest when we arrived. We could even see the name of the guest on some of his garbage on the bed. We got a new room, but the staff did not seem to be especially embarrased or bothered.

In the swimmingpool there was a HUGE lump of hair floating in the water. 5cm by 30 cm in size. Utterly disgusting. It was there the entire day.

2 out of 5 nights they forgot to clean our room while we were out.

The entire hotel is pretty worn down, especially the dining area. If you are too late for breakfast, the cafe serves a joke of a supplement called City Breakfast which consists of a mini-croissant and a disgusting nespresso coffe. The entire hotel only serves nespresso, so if you are looking for quality, this is not the place to stay.

Ill not be visiting Novotel again. Mostly due to the fact that you really feel there is no local management on-site, except for an excel-punching henchman for HQ utterly stripped of power.

If the hotel wishes to improve, a quality management system needs to be in place. It is obviously that it is missing.
